'''利昂·费斯廷格'''（'''Leon Festinger'''，{{bd|1919年|5月8日|1989年|2月11日}}）是一位美国[[社会心理学|社会心理学]]家，以其[[认知失调|认知失调]]理论著称（1957年）。 

在费斯廷格一生中，曾任教于美国多所大学，包括[[爱荷华大学|爱荷华大学]]、[[罗彻斯特大学|罗彻斯特大学]]、[[麻省理工学院|麻省理工学院]]、[[明尼苏达大学|明尼苏达大学]]、[[密歇根大学|密歇根大学]]和[[斯坦福大学|斯坦福大学]]。
<!-- During his years at Stanford in the 1950s and 1960s, he was at the height of his influence,[http://www.uta.edu/psychology/faculty/ickes/ancestry/festinger.htm] and trained many young social psychologists who would proceed to become influential in their own careers (e.g. [[Elliot_Aronson|Elliot Aronson]]). In 1968 he went to the New School for Social Research in New York City, where he remained until his death in 1990. --> 

费斯廷格以其[[认知失调|认知失调]]理论著称。<!-- which suggests that inconsistency among beliefs or behaviors will cause an uncomfortable psychological tension, leading to people to change their beliefs to fit their behavior instead of changing one's behavior to fit their belief, as conventionally assumed. Festinger also proposed [[social_comparison_theory|social comparison theory]], according to which people evaluate their own opinions and desires by comparing themselves with others. -->

== 生平 ==
1919年5月8日，利昂·费斯廷格出生在美国纽约[[布鲁克林|布鲁克林]]一个俄国犹太人移民家庭，父亲亚历克斯·费斯廷格是一位自学成才的刺绣制造商，母亲是萨拉·所罗门· 费斯廷格。利昂·费斯廷格就读于男子中学，1939年，费斯廷格获得[[纽约市立学院|纽约市立学院]]理学士学位，大学毕业后，费斯廷格进入[[爱荷华大学|爱荷华大学]]，在社会心理学之父[[科特·勒温|科特·勒温]]的指导下，1940年获得心理学硕士学位，1942年获博士学位。科特·勒温试图建立心理学的“场论”（类似于物理学），以取代行为主义者的机械论模型。<ref name="anb">Franz Samelson, "[http://www.anb.org/articles/14/14-00887.html Festinger, Leon] {{Wayback|url=http://www.anb.org/articles/14/14-00887.html |date=20080820013743 }}", ''American National Biography Online'', February 2000.</ref>

同年，利昂·费斯廷格与女画家玛丽·奥利弗·Ballou结婚，两人生有3名子女：凯瑟琳、理查德和库尔特。<ref>Stanley Schachter, "[http://books.nap.edu/books/0309049784/html/98.html Leon Festinger] {{Wayback|url=http://books.nap.edu/books/0309049784/html/98.html |date=20080905182710 }}", ''Biographical Memoirs'', 64, 99-111 (National Academy of Sciences, 1994).</ref>) 之后与Ballou离婚, 1968年与 Trudy Bradley结婚。Trudy Bradley 目前为纽约大学教授。

1945年，勒温在麻省理工学院建立了群体动力学研究中心，费斯廷格也到那里担任助理教授。1947年勒温去世后，费斯廷格也离开那里，前往密歇根大学担任副教授。<!--  where he was program director for the Group Dynamics center.<ref name="anb" /> -->

<!-- In 1951 he became a full professor of psychology at 明尼苏达大学. His 1953 book ''Research Methods in the [[Behavioral_Sciences|Behavioral Sciences]]'' (with [[Daniel_Katz|Daniel Katz]]) stressed the need for well-controlled variables in laboratory experiments, even if this meant misinforming the participants.<ref name="anb" />

1955 he moved to 斯坦福大学。Finally, in 1968 he became Staudinger Professor of Psychology at the New School for Social Research in New York.<ref name="anb" />

He remarried the following year to [[Trudy_Bradley|Trudy Bradley]], a professor at the NYU School of Social Work. They had no children.<ref name="anb" /> -->

<!-- ==Example of cognitive dissonance==

''Main article: [[When_Prophecy_Fails|When Prophecy Fails]]''

Festinger's theory of [[cognitive_dissonance|cognitive dissonance]] can account for the psychological consequences of disconfirmed expectations. One of the first published cases of dissonance was reported in the book, ''When Prophecy Fails'' (Festinger et al. 1956). Festinger and his associates read an interesting item in their local newspaper headlined "Prophecy from planet clarion call to city: flee that flood." 

Festinger and his colleagues saw this as a case that would lead to the arousal of dissonance when the prophecy failed. They [[participant_observation|infiltrated]] Mrs. Keech's group and reported the results, confirming their expectations. -->

